  <h3 style="text-decoration: underline;">Find By ID</h3>
  <p>This endpoint returns a single record in the 'Books' collection based on the provided id. The response is a JSON
    representation of the object.</p>

  <p><b>Example URL: </b>http://localhost:3000/api/books/findById/5dd2d0950520905f9b0ad531</p>

  <p><b>Sample Output:</b>
    <pre>
      {
        "_id": "5dd2d0950520905f9b0ad531",
        "name": "Dune",
        "author": "Frank Herbert",
        "genre": "Sci-Fi",
        "__v": 0
      }

    </pre>
  </p>
  <br>

  <h3 style="text-decoration: underline;">Create</h3>
  <p><b>Description: </b>Creates a new record in the 'Books' collection. Uses the provided JSON body to create the new
    record.</p>
  <p><b>Example URL: </b>http://localhost:3000/api/books/create</p>
  <p><b>Sample Input: </b>
    <pre>
        {
          "name":"Catcher in the Rye",
          "author":"JD Salinger",
          "genre":"Fiction"
        }</pre>
  </p>
  <p><b>Sample Output:</b>

    <pre>
        {
          "_id": "5dd2f9e9f1e17e48cccc7c60",
          "name": "Catcher in the Rye",
          "author": "JD Salinger",
          "genre": "Fiction",
          "__v": 0
        }
    </pre>

  </p>

  <br>
  <h3 style="text-decoration: underline;">Update</h3>
  <p><b>Description: </b>Updates a record in the 'Books' collection, based on the ID provided. Uses the JSON body to
    update the record.</p>
  <p><b>Example URL: </b>http://localhost:3000/api/books/update/5dd2f0e331a22934f011869e</p>
  <p><b>Sample Input: </b>
    <pre>
        {
          "name":"Lord of the Flies",
          "author":"William Golding",
          "genre":"Fiction"
        }</pre>
  </p>
  <p><b>Sample Output:</b>
    <pre>
      {
        "_id": "5dd2fd2df1e17e48cccc7c62",
        "name": "Lord of the Flies",
        "author": "William Golding",
        "genre": "Fiction",
        "__v": 0
      }
    </pre>
  </p>

  <br>
  <h3 style="text-decoration: underline;">Delete</h3>
  <p><b>Description: </b>Delets a record in the 'Books' collection based on the ID provided.</p>
  <p><b>Example URL: </b>http://localhost:3000/api/books/delete/5dd2f0e331a22934f011869e</p>
  <p><b>Sample Output:</b>
    <pre>Successfully deleted record with id: 5dd2f0e331a22934f011869e</pre>
  </p>

